  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-nc9-dr01",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team lead",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at MRL 2. The six scoped-out or not-applicable factors are appropriately excluded per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 at this risk level with documented rationale. Low confidence is explicitly documented for the low-flow operating point (2 L/min, 2500 RPM) where the experimental 95% CI spans ±38% due to limited replicates (n=3) and sensitivity of the hemolysis model power-law exponent α. This limitation is accepted as residual risk because: (1) the low-flow point is not the identified worst-case operating condition; (2) the CFD prediction falls within the wide experimental band; (3) the worst-case condition (4 L/min, 3500 RPM) carries only ±12% uncertainty and is well-characterized; and (4) the relative hemolysis index RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied at all operating points with margin. The provenance chain is complete from foundational experimental data through validation results to this decision. No weakeners are asserted.",
